25
00:01:34,165 --> 00:01:38,039
[Nathapatsorn Simasthien, Bhurith Polymeek, Thanaboon Wanlopsirinan, Chayanit Torcharoen]

26
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:40,970
[Executive Producer Warattaya Nilkuha]

27
00:01:40,970 --> 00:01:42,650
[Director Saratswadee Wongsomphet]

28
00:01:45,260 --> 00:01:49,493
Kheetika is my employee, not yours.

29
00:01:49,493 --> 00:01:54,340
You are defending her, not as her boss.

30
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:56,920
It has nothing to do with you.

31
00:01:56,920 --> 00:02:00,828
I want you to remember that if you want to be our spokesperson,

32
00:02:00,828 --> 00:02:03,260
you should stop harassing my employees.

33
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:06,720
Is my grandma back? Why is she in such a hurry to get back, Brother?

34
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:10,020
I'm going to settle what you two have been hiding from me.

35
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:14,820
Are you still pestering Din, Kheetika?

36
00:02:20,670 --> 00:02:23,699
Sira, what do you want to do?

37
00:02:23,699 --> 00:02:26,660
Why did you let this woman work here?

38
00:02:31,620 --> 00:02:37,060
I hired Kheetika because she was capable.

39
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:42,300
But as far as I know, all she's capable of is making trouble.

40
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,651
In particular, when it comes to plagiarism of our company's design.

41
00:02:44,651 --> 00:02:47,146
The plagiarism thing was a misunderstanding.

42
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:51,326
We've found out the truth. Kheetika didn't copy anyone's design.

43
00:02:54,260 --> 00:03:00,260
Here are the sales and growth in the overall market and the New Look website.

44
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:02,493
Since Kheetika came to work,

45
00:03:02,493 --> 00:03:06,005
we've seen a 20% increase in sales.

46
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:14,678
But Kheetika is not the only one who's doing great.

47
00:03:14,678 --> 00:03:16,320
Terminate her employment.

48
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:19,080
I want an explanation. Why are you terminating my employment?

49
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:22,380
I won't allow you to get close to Din.

50
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:27,320
Do you think I will pester Din because I'm close to him?

51
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:36,910
Din and Kheetika have a boss and employee relationship.

52
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,920
Are you sure they are just a boss and his employee?

53
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:46,720
Then... did the man you sent to spy on Din and Kheetika

54
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:50,360
say that they are seeing each other?

55
00:03:54,499 --> 00:03:55,793
Enough.

56
00:03:55,793 --> 00:04:00,300
Grandma, if you want to fire Kheetika, just do it.

57
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:06,060
It's not bad. So I won't be watched.

58
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,720
Then, if we want to meet,

59
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:11,120
we can meet outside.

60
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:16,472
So you don't have to worry about someone telling on us.

61
00:04:16,472 --> 00:04:21,912
I'll have HR compensate Kheetika for three months' salary.

62
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,646
That's the deal, Brother.

63
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:34,210
Din,

64
00:04:34,992 --> 00:04:37,332
I'm not done yet.

65
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:47,168
Din, come back and make it clear.

66
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,668
Din, did you ask the chairwoman to fire Kheetika

67
00:04:59,668 --> 00:05:02,008
because you don't want to follow her lead?

68
00:05:02,008 --> 00:05:03,800
That's right.

69
00:05:04,393 --> 00:05:06,500
Grandma told us that she would come back next week.

70
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,700
But she suddenly appeared in the company.

71
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,848
If you ask me, Grandma must have planned it in advance.

72
00:05:11,848 --> 00:05:13,960
She wanted to catch us off guard.

73
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,640
If I'm right,

74
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:20,140
Grandma might think we'll beg her to not fire Kheetika.

75
00:05:20,140 --> 00:05:23,332
So she could force us to listen to her.

76
00:05:23,332 --> 00:05:25,474
So you made the first move and ruined her plan.

77
00:05:25,474 --> 00:05:26,920
Yes.

78
00:05:27,819 --> 00:05:31,263
I started it. Brother, you wrap it up.

79
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:50,860
[If you believe in me, just play along.]

80
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,940
How much do you want this time?

81
00:05:58,940 --> 00:06:00,998
Tell me.

82
00:06:00,998 --> 00:06:03,608
The money you can offer is just a drop in the bucket.

83
00:06:03,608 --> 00:06:09,540
If I get Din, I can get your money and GU.

84
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:11,480
I can have everything you have.

85
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,860
There's no way. You can't get my stuff.

86
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:16,560
You heard what Din said.

87
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:20,686
Do you think you can stop me by terminating my employment?

88
00:06:20,686 --> 00:06:23,366
We're not laying her off.

89
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:30,071
Ms. Chairwoman, if we fire Kheetika,

90
00:06:30,071 --> 00:06:34,080
we don't know how she will entice Din.

91
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:37,008
So what do you want? Will you fire me or not?

92
00:06:37,008 --> 00:06:39,540
And I want to make it clear that I never enticed Din.

93
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:41,480
What is it?

94
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:45,176
You just agreed with me about terminating her employment.

95
00:06:45,176 --> 00:06:49,472
Sorry, Ms. Chairwoman. It was my mistake to be thoughtless.

96
00:06:49,472 --> 00:06:52,112
But then I thought about it.

97
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,720
Din is about to become the chairman.

98
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:59,100
If we keep Kheetika in sight, we can control Din.

99
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:06,160
At least we can use Kheetika to lure Din back to work.

100
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,638
Just like I'm doing now.

101
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:13,480
Are you sure you can take care of everything?

102
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,140
I'm sure.

103
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:18,740
She has nothing, was abandoned by her mother, and was homeless.

104
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:21,873
I don't think it's difficult to control her.

105
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,006
Brother.

106
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:36,546
Brother, is everything going well?

107
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:42,940
Ms. Chairwoman agreed to let Kheetika continue to work here.

108
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:45,960
See, Brother? I told you our plan would work.

109
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,751
What do you want to do?

110
00:07:48,751 --> 00:07:53,400
I think I want to start over with Kheetika again.

111
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,530
What?

112
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:57,500
I want to start over with Kheetika again.

113
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:05,160
- Please call me back.
- Thank you.

114
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:09,011
Has anyone reached him?

115
00:08:09,011 --> 00:08:11,440
- He's not in the warehouse.
- He's not in the mall.

116
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,790
He's not in the cafeteria.

117
00:08:14,893 --> 00:08:17,000
Where did Maha go?

118
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,108
Why didn't he answer the phone?

119
00:08:19,108 --> 00:08:20,700
If Maha is not here,

120
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,870
we can't know why the chairwoman

121
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:29,140
summonsed Khun Sira, Khun Din, and Khun Kheetika.

122
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:34,060
You don't care why Maha is not there. But you care about an unimportant thing.

123
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:35,621
No, this is important.

124
00:08:35,621 --> 00:08:38,080
I have bad feelings about it.

125
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,665
Maha has never left his job.

126
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,871
Where have you been today?

127
00:08:52,871 --> 00:08:54,858
You didn't answer my call.

128
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:03,446
Hey, you. I'm asking you. Didn't you hear me?

129
00:09:03,446 --> 00:09:05,530
Where can I go?

130
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:07,340
I'm homeless and abandoned by my mom.

131
00:09:07,340 --> 00:09:09,660
Of course, I should come back here to work.

132
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:11,538
Is there anything else you want to ask?

133
00:09:11,538 --> 00:09:15,858
Hey. I can explain what happened today.

134
00:09:15,858 --> 00:09:17,420
I said that because─

135
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:22,780
Because you owe Khun Premyuda a debt, you wanted to please her.

136
00:09:26,506 --> 00:09:29,333
Did you see the message I sent you?

137
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:33,360
[If you believe in me, just play along.]

138
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,440
What is it, Rossarin?

139
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:52,780
Rossarin, calm down. Speak slowly.

140
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:55,100
What's wrong with Maha?

141
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,980
Okay, I'll be right there.

142
00:09:57,980 --> 00:09:59,905
What's wrong?

143
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,180
How's it going?

144
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:10,660
Horrible.

145
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,840
Maha.

146
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:21,993
Rossarin, Maha smells like alcohol.

147
00:10:21,993 --> 00:10:23,640
What happened? How did this happen?

148
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,934
His girlfriend wanted to break up with him.

149
00:10:25,934 --> 00:10:27,166
Why?

150
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,666
It's all because of Khun Sira.

151
00:10:30,746 --> 00:10:34,250
I broke up with my girlfriend because of Khun Sira.

152
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:39,733
It's all Khun Sira's fault that my girlfriend dumped me.

153
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:44,280
Maha, what do I have to do with you breaking up with your girlfriend?

154
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,730
It's your fault.

155
00:10:45,730 --> 00:10:48,650
Because you order me around all the time.

156
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:50,500
You call me in the early hours of the morning.

157
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:54,100
If you hurt somewhere, you ask me to take care of you.

158
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:58,320
You ask me to talk and eat with you.

159
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,540
I don't have time for my girlfriend.

160
00:11:00,540 --> 00:11:03,500
So she dumped me.

161
00:11:05,725 --> 00:11:08,872
It's all your fault. You are responsible for him.

162
00:11:10,660 --> 00:11:12,300
What should I do?

163
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:15,020
Maha's girlfriend dumped him because you always boss him around.

164
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:17,760
You have to explain it to his girlfriend.

165
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,000
What do you want me to explain?

166
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,480
I didn't do anything wrong.

167
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:25,558
You're the one responsible for his girlfriend breaking up with him.

168
00:11:25,558 --> 00:11:29,060
You're a bad boss. Are you self-aware?

169
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,920
You never think about others.

170
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,920
You only care about yourself.

171
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,760
You are so selfish.

172
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:37,040
- You're ruthless.
- Hey, you!

173
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,680
Excuse me.

174
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:43,400
I asked you here to help, not fight.

175
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:50,020
Oh, where is Maha?

176
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:54,560
Maha? Maha!

177
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,980
- Let go.
- No.

178
00:11:58,226 --> 00:11:59,500
Let it go.

179
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,080
- Maha!
- Let go!

180
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,860
Maha, what are you doing? Give the flowers back to her.

181
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,703
Let go.

182
00:12:04,703 --> 00:12:07,540
Trust me. If you don't want to be like me, just break up.

183
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:09,680
Everyone's love is different.

184
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:15,520
- Not every relationship is destined to break up.
- Yes.

185
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:18,440
It's all the same. You will break up, no matter how much you love each other.

186
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:19,620
Just like us.

187
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:21,800
Like Khun Kheetika and Khun Sasa.

188
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:24,360
Every couple will break up in the end.

189
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,980
Maha! Stop talking nonsense.

190
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,280
Give the flowers back.

191
00:12:30,785 --> 00:12:32,718
All right.

192
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:37,200
- We're sorry.
- We're sorry.

193
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:42,780
Bye-bye.

194
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:53,600
- Maha!
- Maha!

195
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,660
What are you going to do?

196
00:13:05,492 --> 00:13:07,352
Maha!

197
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,920
Khun Sira!

198
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:27,720
Are you done, Maha?

199
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:31,480
Look. Khun Sira is all wet because of you.

200
00:13:32,886 --> 00:13:34,900
I'm sorry, Khun Sira.

201
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,580
I did that because I was drunk and lost my mind.

202
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:39,760
I hope you learned your lesson.

203
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:42,200
You should remember what you did while drunk.

204
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:45,520
Regarding your girlfriend, I'm sorry to you.

205
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:48,760
I'm sorry I caused you to break up.

206
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:52,380
If you want me to explain to her, just tell me.

207
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,637
I'll explain to her.

208
00:13:53,637 --> 00:13:55,740
Forget it, Khun Sira.

209
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:57,380
You don't have to explain.

210
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:59,900
She went abroad with her new boyfriend.

211
00:14:03,978 --> 00:14:06,612
Did she have a new boyfriend just after you broke up?

212
00:14:07,306 --> 00:14:09,946
They started dating before we broke up.

213
00:14:09,946 --> 00:14:11,990
I didn't have time for her.

214
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:14,466
So she went out with another man.

215
00:14:14,466 --> 00:14:18,433
After I found out, she broke up with me.

216
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:20,060
For a woman who dated two men at the same time,

217
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,827
you shouldn't be sad or sorry.

218
00:14:22,827 --> 00:14:27,040
Why didn't you tell me that you wanted to spend more time with your girlfriend?

219
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:30,048
Because I'm worried about you. I don't want you to be alone

220
00:14:30,048 --> 00:14:35,360
when you are sick and when you are in trouble. You are always alone.

221
00:14:37,646 --> 00:14:40,073
You don't need to worry about me.

222
00:14:40,073 --> 00:14:42,486
I'm used to being alone.

223
00:14:42,486 --> 00:14:45,240
No one will be used to living alone.

224
00:14:52,220 --> 00:14:56,060
I don't know how to make it up to you.

225
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:59,329
I'll give you some time off.

226
00:14:59,329 --> 00:15:02,132
You can come back to work when you feel better.

227
00:15:02,132 --> 00:15:03,435
No.

228
00:15:03,435 --> 00:15:05,600
What will you do if I take some time off?

229
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:08,880
How will you handle your work and life?

230
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:11,360
It's all right, Maha. Don't worry.

231
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,860
I can take care of myself.

232
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:15,180
Even if I rest, I can't feel at ease.

233
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:17,773
- Are you yelling at me?
- I'm not.

234
00:15:17,773 --> 00:15:21,380
- But─
- Stop arguing. I'll take care of Khun Sira for you.

235
00:15:26,265 --> 00:15:28,500
What's wrong?

236
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,992
Do you think I can't take care of him?

237
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,532
I made you some porridge.

238
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,708
Remember to take the medicine after eating the porridge.

239
00:15:50,708 --> 00:15:54,740
I've got you some cold medicine, fever medicine, allergy medicine,

240
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:57,220
and anti-diarrheal medicine.

241
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:58,207
Wait.

242
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:02,040
Why did you get me anti-diarrheal medicine? I don't have diarrhea.

243
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,080
Just...

244
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:07,200
in case you get diarrhea from my porridge.

